(1646, 287, 'synopsis', 'This lesson provides participants with an opportunity to explore the impact their Families of Origin (FoO) have had on their positive and challenging experience(s) of self and others, especially around racial and sexual orientation identities. Specifically, participants will create a genogram, a type of psychological family tree where they map FoO generations, including critical FoO events, family legacies, and loyalty conflicts. Exploring FoOs will allow participants to identify both risk and protective factors within their families.'),
