(3539, 399, 'synopsis', 'This lesson encourages participants to examine their relationships in order to seek social support after a positive HIV diagnosis. Through personal reflection, role play, and group discussion, participants will identify people in their life to provide social support, identify what social support they need; and practice HIV disclosure.\r\n\r\n<em>Though not required, this lesson is best utilized in conjunction with the lesson, “Healthy Sexuality after a Positive Diagnosis: My Relationship with Self.”</em>'),
