(5279, 473, 'synopsis', 'This lesson encourages participants to examine their relationships in order to seek social support after a positive HIV diagnosis. Through personal reflection, role play, and group discussion, participants will identify people in their life to provide social support, identify what social support they need; and practice HIV disclosure.\r\n\r\n<em>Though not required, this lesson is best utilized in conjunction with the lesson, “Healthy Sexuality after a Positive Diagnosis: My Relationship with Self.”</em>'),
(5280, 473, '_synopsis', 'field_5eaf33260b6fb'),
(5281, 473, 'objectives', '<ul>\r\n 	<li>Identify five people in their life to provide social support.</li>\r\n 	<li>Identify the emotional, moral, practical, recreational, and mentoring social support they need.</li>\r\n 	<li>Describe the emotional, moral, practical, recreational, and mentoring social support they need.</li>\r\n 	<li>Practice HIV disclosure by engaging in a role play activity.</li>\r\n 	<li>Describe how they will seek social support.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
