(28, 1, '2020-04-23 10:08:13', '2020-04-23 10:08:13', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The SWAG Toolkit is a collection of lesson plans designed to support Black men in improving their overall well-being, whether directly via community member-oriented holistic sexuality education, or indirectly via provider-oriented competency training. We were guided by their voices and their needs and included authors from the community or with extensive experience working in the community.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Swag” is a word used to describe how a person presents themselves to the world, with confidence and sophistication and in a way that earns respect and credibility. Our goal has been to provide Black gay and bisexual men with sexual health resources that empower them and support them holistically so they can be confident in making decisions about their sexual health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":27,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://swagtoolkit.test/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/icon-toolkit.svg\" alt=\"Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-27\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Relevant sex education materials for Black gay and bisexual men', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-23 10:08:13', '2020-04-23 10:08:13', '', 2, 'http://swagtoolkit.test/2020/04/23/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
